 A</span></td>\n<td style=\"background:#ede3c8;width:25.239%;height:17px\">Untrained</td>\n<td style=\"background:#ede3c8;width:182.115%;height:17px\">Palming a small, unattended object without being noticed requires you to roll a single Thievery check against the Perception DCs of all creatures who are currently observing you.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:15px\">\n<td style=\"background:#f5efe0;width:25.1923%;height:17px\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.RDXXE7wMrSPCLv5k]{Steal}<span style=\"font-family:'Pathfinder2eActions';font-size:1.5em\"> A</span></td>\n<td style=\"background:#f5efe0;width:25.239%;height:17px\">Untrained</td>\n<td style=\"background:#f5efe0;width:182.115%;height:17px\">You try to take a small object from another creature without being noticed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:15px\">\n<td style=\"background:#ede3c8;width:25.1923%;height:17px\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.cYdz2grcOcRt4jk6]{Disable Device}<span style=\"font-family:'Pathfinder2eActions';font-size:1.5em\"> D</span></td>\n<td style=\"background:#ede3c8;width:25.239%;height:17px\">Trained</td>\n<td style=\"background:#ede3c8;width:182.115%;height:17px\">This action allows you to disarm a trap or another complex device.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:15px\">\n<td style=\"background:#f5efe0;width:25.1923%;height:17px\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.2EE4aF4SZpYf0R6H]{Pick a Lock}<span style=\"font-family:'Pathfinder2eActions';font-size:1.5em\"> D</span></td>\n<td style=\"background:#f5efe0;width:25.239%;height:17px\">Trained</td>\n<td style=\"background:#f5efe0;width:182.115%;height:17px\">Opening a lock without a key is very similar to Disabling a Device, but the DC of the check is determined by the complexity and construction of the lock you are attempting to pick (locks and their DCs are found on page 290).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"VKxey0ejFGz07TYB":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.PF2eGMScreen.tres-gm-screen.4tJJGs